    <string name="click_to_add_images">Swipe:Select | Drag:Place/Del</string>
    <string name="instructions_content">[Add Images]\n• From Gallery: Tap the "Add" button in the pending area to select images from gallery\n• Image Package: Tap Function Menu → "Image Package", select "Import Local Package" to import ZIP file (password protected supported), or select "Select Built-in Package" to import preset package\n• Import Target Selection: When importing package, choose to import to "Pending Characters" or "Character Badges" area\n\n[Pending Area Operations]\n• Swipe left/right: Browse images in the pending area\n• Drag down: Drag image to target tier and release to place\n• Drag up to delete: Drag image upward beyond the pending area top (image turns red) and release to delete\n• Tap Add: Tap "Add" button to import images from gallery\n• Tap Clear: Tap "Clear" button to delete all pending images\n\n[Tier Operations]\n• Edit Name: Single-tap the left color block, enter new name and confirm\n• Change Color: Double-tap the left color block to select preset colors or enter hex color code\n• Delete Tier: Swipe left or right on the tier, release when it turns red to delete\n• Add Tier: Tap the + button at the bottom to add a new tier\n• Tier Sorting: Vertical drag (drag up/down) the left color block to adjust tier order\n\n[Tier Image Operations]\n• Single-tap: Open image action menu (View/Crop/Move/Replace/Rename/Set Badges)\n• Double-tap: Select image (blue border appears), then double-tap another image to swap positions (cross-tier supported)\n• Vertical drag: Drag up/down to move between tiers or back to pending area\n• Drag up to delete: Drag image upward beyond the pending area top (image turns red) and release to delete\n• Move Position: Select "Move" in image action menu to move image to another tier, or use "Move Left/Right" buttons to fine-tune position\n\n[Image Action Menu]\n• View: View full image and resolution info\n• Crop: Choose 1:1 or 3:4 ratio, or custom pixel size\n• Move: Move image to another tier, or adjust position in current tier (First/Last)\n• Replace: Select a new image to replace current one\n• Rename: Add a name to the image, displayed at the bottom\n• Badges: Add up to 3 badges, select badge position (1/2/3 slot)\n\n[Badges]\n• Select "Badges" in image action menu to set\n• Up to 3 badges per image\n• Display at top-right corner by default\n• Enable "External Badge" mode in Program Settings to display badges on the right side of image\n• Package Import: Import package directly to badge area for use as badges\n• Select from Preview: Tap badge slot to select from imported badge list\n• Delete Badge: Tap delete button on the right side of badge to remove it\n\n[Manage Presets]\nTap Function Menu → "Manage Presets":\n• Save Preset: Save current tier list configuration as preset file\n• Import Preset: Select .tdds format preset file to import\n• Export Preset: Export current configuration as .tdds file to share\n• Preset List: View, apply or delete saved presets\n• Overwrite Prompt: Choose to overwrite or create new when importing existing preset\n\n[Draft Auto-Save]\n• Auto-save: App automatically saves current editing state in background\n• Restore Prompt: Prompt to restore unsaved draft when reopening app\n• Manual Save: Press Home key or switch to other apps triggers draft save\n\n[Other Features]\n• Edit Title: Tap top title to modify tier list name\n• Edit Author: Tap "Created by: Author" to modify author name\n• Save: Tap bottom save button, preview then save to gallery\n• Share: Choose to share image before saving\n• Reset: Tap bottom reset button to restore default tiermaster\n• Theme Toggle: Tap top-left theme button to switch light/dark theme\n• Function Menu: Tap top-right menu icon, includes Image Package, Manage Presets, Program Settings, Instructions, Support Author, About\n• Resource Management: Tap top-right resource icon to view app cache and working directory size, and clean cache\n\n[Program Settings]\n• Disable Click-Add: When enabled, tapping pending area images won\'t add directly to tier\n• External Badge: When enabled, badges display on right side of image instead of top-right corner\n• Change Language: Switch interface language\n• Adjust Float: Adjust position offset of drag preview\n• Default Theme: When enabled, follow system theme to auto switch light/dark mode</string>
